61 High Priestess</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=honeycut22>Honeycut22</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(6/9/03 11:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Congratulations Hawkestone.. The New Most-Hated Guild on</span><hr size=1> So now you cant play the game the way you want to?? why??I'm not real clear how they are comtroling your computer.. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=honeycut22>Honeycut22</A> at: 6/9/03 11:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalionbuscador>XalionBuscador</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#330000>(6/9/03 11:38 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Congratulations Hawkestone.. The New Most-Hated Guild on</span><hr size=1> I read a piece a while back about how video games are contributing to the moral degradation of society.<br>
<br>
You see - the main contention was that video games are a realm without consequences.  You die, your character gets back up and you keep going.  You screw someone over - who cares?  After all its just a game.<br>
<br>
They contended that it is becomming more apparent now because MMRPGs take that one step further - now, you are actually screwing real people over instead of just pixels on a computer.  However, you can still sing the &quot;Its just a game&quot; mantra - you don't have to take responsibility for your actions.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think a lot of that is utter bullshit.  I think that those threatening RL violence against Hawkestone members need to step away from the game and reevaluate things a bit.  However, I do agree with the part that just because it is on the computer and not in person does NOT abrogate your responsibility.  I try really hard to treat everyone in the game with the same respect that I would give a person standing in front of me.  There is someone sitting in front of a computer playing that toon - they deserve to be treated like a person.<br>
<br>
Hawkestone STILL must face the consequences for their actions.  Saying &quot;its just a game&quot; is a fancy way of saying &quot;none of you cocksmoking assholes matter - its all about ME and the way I want things done&quot;.  The attempt to say the rest of us are doing the same thing is feeble at best.  Every guild who has gone through sleeper's tomb up to this point was given the option of waking the sleeper.  Every guild up to this point has decided that the choice was not theirs to make for the server.  Each guild has left the sleeper sleeping out of respect for those who have gone before and consideration for those who will go after.<br>
<br>
Until now that is.  Whatever - convince yourself that just because EQ is a game, it removes all moral responsibility for your choices.  However, as far as I'm concerned, I'm just going to ignore you exist.  Sure, if faced with a situation where I can't ignore you, I'd probably still give you a rez or a summon.  But thats because I'd help someone I hated in real life as well.  I can however guarentee I'll never group with you - I don't trust you people any more.<br>
<br>
One of the saddest things I've ever seen is when I logged in and did a /who all Hawkestone and saw someone who helped me make my level 39 spell DMF in ST recovering his corpse.  Destroyed any illusion I had on how he was a nice guy who thought about other people first.<br>
